other_tests.findings: The genetic results indicated a pathogenic missense variant identified in apparent homozygosis in the PSAT1 gene, associated with Neu-Laxova Syndrome-2 (NLS-2) by autosomal recessive inheritance.
Several abnormalities were revealed including absent cavum septum pellucidum, an abnormal bridge of tissue across the midline, hypoplastic cerebellum, and mild ocular proptosis among others.

other_tests.procedure_name: Cytomegalovirus (CMV) and toxoplasma PCR in amniotic fluid
